{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "Example 1", "heading_level": 6, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows data from tiered testing of antidrug antibody (ADA).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Tiered testing scheme for ADA evaluation generally includes the following steps: screening, confirmatory, and \"characterization\" of the antidrug antibody.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In tier 1, all evaluable samples are run in a screening assay.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Samples that are positive for ADA in the screen assay are then analyzed in a confirmatory assay (tier 2).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The samples that are positive for ADA in both the screen and confirmatory tiers of testing are further tested in tier 3.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This frequently includes analysis of antibody titer and neutralizing activity.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "In order to distinguish the distinctive differences between the 3 tiers of ADA testing, the standard variable ISTSACDGNT is used to represent the controlled values SCREEN, CONFIRM, and QUANTIFY.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "These values help to describe the operational objective or the reason behind each testing step tier, and also to provide uniqueness to each row of records or related to each other; in this particular case, tests are done in a tiered, sequential manner from screen to confirm to quantification of the detected antidrug antibody.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Lastly, antibody titer is often defined as the reciprocal of the lowest dilution of a sample generating a signal that is above the assay cut-point.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0233_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 233, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "§6.3.5.5 Immunogenicity Specimen Assessments (IS)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Alternatively, the titer is defined as the reciprocal of the dilution of a sample generating a signal equivalent to the assay cut-point, calculated by an interpolation formula provided in an assay specific bioanalytical method.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.2_drift_cal", "ts": "2026-04-26T00:00:00Z"}}
